                "minimum_value": 1.5,
                "maximum_value": 10.5,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the uncertainty from averaging of",
                " the individual results over the whole sample area as",
                "well as statistical errors. The latter dominate the low",
                "isotope ratios, whereas systematic errors affect the",
                "higher cross-sections."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR2",
                "minimum_value": 2.5,
                "maximum_value": 50.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron energy in the near-",
                "threshold region was assumed to be known to better than",
                " 40-KeV. This leads to an additional uncertainty of",
                "0.8-mb for a neutron energy of 13.8-MeV. It corresponds",
                "to an error of about 50% at 13.8-MeV and about 25% at",
                "13.9-MeV and reflects the steeply raising shape of the",
                " excitation function near threshold. For the higher-",
                "energy region, a 20-KeV uncertainty was assumed, which",
                "corresponds to absolute uncertainties of 0.6-mb, i.e.",
                "10% at 14-MeV neutron energy and 2.4% for 14.8-MeV."
              ]
            },
